value.title: Federal judge throws out Gohmert lawsuit asking Pence to interfere in Electoral College count
value.excerpt: A federal judge threw out a lawsuit from Rep. Louie Gohmert of Texas and several Arizona Republicans seeking to force Vice President Mike Pence to help throw the election to President Donald Trump next week when Congress meets to count the Electoral College votes.

value.title: Biden's inaugural committee hosting national memorial for Covid-19 victims on January 19
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden's inaugural committee on Thursday announced that it is hosting a national memorial to remember and honor the lives lost to Covid-19 and is asking cities and towns around the country to participate.

value.title: Trump was briefed that China sought to pay non-state actors to attack US forces in Afghanistan
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump received information earlier this month that China sought to pay non-state actors to attack American forces in Afghanistan, a senior administration official said.

value.title: Biden names Kathleen Hicks as first woman deputy defense secretary
value.excerpt: Joe Biden's transition team announced Wednesday that former Obama Pentagon official Kathleen Hicks is the President-elect's pick to serve as deputy secretary of defense, and she would be the first woman to serve in the role if confirmed by the Senate.

value.title: Trump administration to block palm oil from second company in Malaysia over forced labor findings
value.excerpt: The Trump administration will halt imports of palm oil from Malaysia over findings of forced labor abuses at the plantations of one of the country's top producers of the product, which is found in many everyday items.

value.title: Here's how Mitch McConnell is planning to kill Trump's $2,000 checks
value.excerpt: Less than 48 hours after President Donald Trump claimed that "the Senate will start the process for a vote that increases checks to $2,000, repeals Section 230, and starts an investigation into voter fraud," the actual boss of the Senate had his say.

value.title: How Richard Jewell’s Lawyer Became a Pro-Trump Conspiracy Theorist
value.excerpt: The defamation lawyer L. Lin Wood has transformed into a fierce advocate for President Trump whose error-riddled lawsuits have promoted falsehoods about election fraud.

value.title: Kamala Harris receives first dose of Moderna Covid-19 vaccine on camera
value.excerpt: Vice President-elect Kamala Harris is expected to receive the first dose of a Covid-19 vaccine on Tuesday, according to the Biden transition team.

value.title: Trump, Michelle Obama top Gallup's 2020 most admired lists
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump and former first lady Michelle Obama are the most admired man and woman of 2020, according to a new Gallup poll released Tuesday.

value.title: Biden eyes cuts to Trump nuclear program as critical arms control deadline with Russia looms

value.title: Trump opens up federal dollars for private school vouchers amid pandemic
value.excerpt: The White House said that the order would give states new flexibility in how they use federal block grant programs that provide money for a wide range of community services.

value.title: Walter Reed doctor who criticized Trump's hospital drive-by works last shift after being removed from schedule
value.excerpt: Dr. James Phillips, an emergency room doctor at Walter Reed National Military Medical Center, has been removed from his duty after publicly criticizing President Donald Trump's drive-by around the hospital after his coronavirus diagnosis.

value.title: Biden to deliver remarks on foreign policy and national security Monday
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden is expected to deliver remarks on Monday afternoon after receiving a briefing from members of his national security and foreign policy agency review teams.

value.excerpt: "Since we can't see each other in person, using memes to kind of share feelings and connect with one another has become huge this year," said the editor of Know Your Meme.

value.excerpt: For Christmas this year, Washington is giving the country more pain.

value.excerpt: The proposal under consideration calls for the federal government to cover the cost of providing tests to K-12 schools throughout the country.

value.title: The ‘Trump Bump’ for Books Has Been Significant. Can It Continue?
value.excerpt: As a new administration looms, publishers have snapped up another crop of forthcoming Trump books by prominent journalists and pundits.

value.title: California conservatives rebuke Trump pardon of Duncan Hunter
value.excerpt: Trump granted a full pardon Tuesday to Hunter, who was set to begin an 11-month sentence at a federal prison in two weeks after pleading guilty to stealing campaign funds for personal use.

value.title: Trump issues 26 new pardons, including ones for Stone, Manafort and Charles Kushner
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump on Wednesday evening announced 26 new pardons, including ones for longtime ally Roger Stone, former campaign chairman Paul Manafort and White House senior adviser Jared Kushner's father, Charles.

value.title: Congressional GOP grapples with 'unhinged' Trump
value.excerpt: Even in his waning days in power, President Donald Trump is still finding ways to inflict his signature loyalty tests on the Republican Party.

value.title: George Clooney on ‘The Midnight Sky’ and Donald Trump
value.excerpt: His new movie is on Netflix, but the actor-director says theaters won’t go away and Hollywood will be fine. He’s not so sure about Washington.

value.title: Listen to Trump's sudden stipulation for Covid-19 stimulus bill
value.excerpt: President Trump issued a sudden pre-Christmas demand for changes to a desperately needed $900 billion pandemic relief bill that could potentially risk shattering the bipartisan compromise reached by Democrats and Republicans. CNN's Joe Johns reports.

value.title: Trump administration considering granting Saudi prince legal immunity for alleged assassination plot, sources say
value.excerpt: The Trump administration is considering granting Saudi Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman legal immunity from a federal lawsuit alleging that he ordered an assassination squad to kill a former top Saudi intelligence official who shared information with the US, according to sources familiar with the situation.

value.title: Lev Parnas files motion to dismiss, says he was selectively prosecuted to protect Trump
value.excerpt: Lev Parnas, the indicted associate of Rudy Giuliani, has filed a motion to dismiss the campaign finance charges against him, arguing he has been selectively prosecuted and blocked from providing information to lawmakers seeking to impeach President Trump.
